From: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
Date: Fri, 19 Jun 2026 00:00:00 -0700
Subject: [PATCH] Skip redundant ONNX opset registration when static
 registration is enabled

This build links the system ONNX shared library, which is compiled
WITHOUT __ONNX_DISABLE_STATIC_REGISTRATION. ONNX therefore lazily
auto-registers the standard ai.onnx / ai.onnx.ml (and training) opsets
the first time its schema map is accessed -- which, in
Environment::Initialize(), already happens when the contrib and
com.ms.internal.nhwc opsets are registered just above this point.

onnxruntime additionally calls RegisterOnnxOperatorSetSchema() (and the
ML / training variants) unconditionally. With an auto-registering ONNX
this registers every standard operator a second time, so ONNX floods
stderr with hundreds of lines like:

  Schema error: Trying to register schema with name Abs (domain: 
  version: 1) ... but it is already registered ...

ONNX documents the contract for this in onnx/defs/operator_sets.h: when
static registration is enabled (IsOnnxStaticRegistrationDisabled()
returns false) the linking module must not call the registration
methods again. Guard the explicit calls accordingly; they still run when
ONNX is built with static registration disabled (upstream's bundled
configuration).

Upstream-Status: Inappropriate [OE-specific: depends on linking a
system ONNX built with static registration enabled]
Signed-off-by: Ilies CHERGUI <ichergui@nvidia.com>
---
diff --git a/onnxruntime/core/session/environment.cc b/onnxruntime/core/session/environment.cc
index 523ff8eaf13..9b6eefcd3e8 100644
--- a/onnxruntime/core/session/environment.cc
+++ b/onnxruntime/core/session/environment.cc
@@ -303,15 +303,27 @@ Status Environment::Initialize(std::unique_ptr<logging::LoggingManager> logging_
 #ifdef USE_DML
       dml::RegisterDmlSchemas();
 #endif
-      RegisterOnnxOperatorSetSchema();
+      // This build links a system ONNX that is compiled WITHOUT
+      // __ONNX_DISABLE_STATIC_REGISTRATION, so ONNX lazily auto-registers the
+      // standard ai.onnx / ai.onnx.ml (and training) opsets the first time its
+      // schema map is accessed (which already happened above when the contrib /
+      // NHWC opsets were registered). Per ONNX's documented contract in
+      // onnx/defs/operator_sets.h, a linking module must NOT also call these
+      // registration functions when static registration is enabled, otherwise
+      // every standard operator is registered twice and ONNX floods stderr with
+      // "Schema error: ... already registered". Register explicitly only when
+      // ONNX was built with static registration disabled.
+      if (IsOnnxStaticRegistrationDisabled()) {
+        RegisterOnnxOperatorSetSchema();
 
 #ifndef DISABLE_ML_OPS
-      RegisterOnnxMLOperatorSetSchema();
+        RegisterOnnxMLOperatorSetSchema();
 #endif
 
 #if defined(ENABLE_TRAINING_OPS)
-      RegisterOnnxTrainingOperatorSetSchema();
+        RegisterOnnxTrainingOperatorSetSchema();
 #endif
+      }
 
 #if defined(ENABLE_TRAINING_OPS)
       // preserve this order until <training schemas>: this depends on operatorsetschema registration.
